{
  "texts": [
    "Benchmark tasks will also require a trustworthy mechanism for users to submit their model's results and have them validated.",
    "To ensure fair comparisons, users must adhere to a clear set of rules.",
    "There are several potential approaches for managing this process, each with its own trade-offs, we outline these in Table 2.",
    "The solution can act as a data repository (e.g., UCI Machine Learning Repository) and results are validated indirectly via academic peer review.",
    "Rigorous academic peer review but slow and not standardized."
  ]
}